WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.845 --> 00:00:14.264
[Lin] Wow. Sounds like a rough night.

2
00:00:14.264 --> 00:00:16.683
[George] I mean. we've had bad fights.

3
00:00:16.683 --> 00:00:18.309
It's been a while.

4
00:00:18.309 --> 00:00:20.061
Definitely before June was born.

5
00:00:20.729 --> 00:00:23.148
But I don't know. I just...

6
00:00:23.940 --> 00:00:26.025
I don't understand why she was so angry.

7
00:00:26.025 --> 00:00:29.612
No. and like I said.
that was totally out of line.

8
00:00:30.447 --> 00:00:31.781
[George] Honestly?

9
00:00:32.741 --> 00:00:35.326
I can't even enjoy anything vanilla
since her comment.

10
00:00:35.326 --> 00:00:36.286
[Amy] I'm sorry.

11
00:00:36.995 --> 00:00:39.664
I've just been really stressed
about the deal.

12
00:00:40.248 --> 00:00:41.958
But it won't happen again.

13
00:00:43.043 --> 00:00:45.336
I've found ways to manage my stress.

14
00:00:45.837 --> 00:00:47.839
What have you found works for you?

15
00:00:50.633 --> 00:00:52.802
[Amy] <i><font color="#80FFFF">Well. you know. I just close my eyes</i></font>

16
00:00:52.802 --> 00:00:55.972
<i><font color="#80FFFF">and clear my head.
and focus on my breathing.</i></font>

17
00:00:55.972 --> 00:00:57.515
Stupid yuppy-ass house.

18
00:00:57.515 --> 00:01:00.018
[Amy] <i><font color="#80FFFF">My mind wanders
to some silly places sometimes</i></font>

19
00:01:00.018 --> 00:01:02.187
<i><font color="#80FFFF">- but it's okay.</i></font>
- Fuck!

20
00:01:02.187 --> 00:01:04.230
[Amy] <i><font color="#80FFFF">The human brain. wow. right?</i></font>

21
00:01:08.526 --> 00:01:09.652
That's great. Amy.

22
00:01:10.403 --> 00:01:13.198
[George] I've been telling her
to meditate for years.

23
00:01:13.198 --> 00:01:15.408
I've sent her so many links.

24
00:01:15.408 --> 00:01:17.619
And thank you for the links. George.

25
00:01:18.244 --> 00:01:20.955
George. have you noticed a change?

26
00:01:20.955 --> 00:01:24.667
I mean. we've been doing better
since the fight.

27
00:01:25.668 --> 00:01:30.548
But all those things she said
can't be coming out of nowhere. right?

28
00:01:30.548 --> 00:01:33.718
I mean. got to dig a little deeper.

29
00:01:34.302 --> 00:01:35.136
Right?

30
00:01:36.221 --> 00:01:39.140
[Lin] Now. Amy. when he says that

31
00:01:39.140 --> 00:01:43.269
and you hear him saying that.
what does that make you want to say?

32
00:01:44.938 --> 00:01:46.314
Cards on the table?

33
00:01:48.191 --> 00:01:49.567
I wanna say he's right.

34
00:01:52.403 --> 00:01:54.447
<i><font color="#80FFFF">You know. my dad held a lot in.</i></font>

35
00:01:55.198 --> 00:01:59.536
<i><font color="#80FFFF">Chinese guy from the Midwest.
I mean. communication wasn't his forte.</i></font>

36
00:02:01.496 --> 00:02:06.501
<i><font color="#80FFFF">He'd just bottle up everything inside
until it just exploded out at once.</i></font>

37
00:02:06.501 --> 00:02:07.669
Fuck!

38
00:02:07.669 --> 00:02:10.338
Fucking God!

39
00:02:10.839 --> 00:02:13.591
[Amy] <i><font color="#80FFFF">My mom. she wasn't any better.</i></font>

40
00:02:14.843 --> 00:02:15.677
Fuck!

41
00:02:15.677 --> 00:02:17.804
[Amy] <i><font color="#80FFFF">She thought that talking
about your feelings</i></font>

42
00:02:17.804 --> 00:02:19.597
<i><font color="#80FFFF">was the same thing as complaining.</i></font>

43
00:02:19.597 --> 00:02:22.016
<i><font color="#80FFFF">She told me the first time
she heard birds singing</i></font>

44
00:02:22.016 --> 00:02:23.893
<i><font color="#80FFFF">was when she came to America.</i></font>

45
00:02:23.893 --> 00:02:28.148
<i><font color="#80FFFF">because during the Vietnam War.
they ate all the birds.</i></font>

46
00:02:28.148 --> 00:02:32.402
<i><font color="#80FFFF">Can you imagine
what that does to a person? No birds.</i></font>

47
00:02:34.529 --> 00:02:35.864
It's hard to admit. but...

48
00:02:36.614 --> 00:02:40.827
I think growing up with my parents
taught me to repress all my feelings.

49
00:02:43.163 --> 00:02:44.789
- Breakthrough moment. babe.
- No.

50
00:02:45.790 --> 00:02:48.293
Amy. that's very...

51
00:02:49.502 --> 00:02:50.920
self-aware.

52
00:02:50.920 --> 00:02:52.130
Thank you.

53
00:02:52.130 --> 00:02:54.382
[Lin] You know. when we're stressed.

54
00:02:54.382 --> 00:02:57.594
we revert to the pathways
we created as children.

55
00:02:57.594 --> 00:02:59.888
No. Yeah. I mean.
it all comes down to parents

56
00:02:59.888 --> 00:03:02.807
and I'm excited to dig into that.

57
00:03:02.807 --> 00:03:06.352
But acknowledging this
is just the first step.

58
00:03:07.186 --> 00:03:09.772
In order to create new neural pathways.

59
00:03:09.772 --> 00:03:14.110
we have to uncover
what lies underneath our awareness.

60
00:03:15.612 --> 00:03:16.654
Right.

61
00:03:17.697 --> 00:03:19.365
<i><font color="#80FFFF">I think maybe subconsciously</i></font>

62
00:03:19.365 --> 00:03:23.369
<i><font color="#80FFFF">that's why I leave most of
Junie's caretaking in George's hands.</i></font>

63
00:03:23.369 --> 00:03:27.165
<i><font color="#80FFFF">Maybe part of me is afraid
that I'll create in Junie the same. uh...</i></font>

64
00:03:27.165 --> 00:03:28.791
<i><font color="#80FFFF">What was it you called it?</i></font>

65
00:03:28.791 --> 00:03:31.794
<i><font color="#80FFFF">...neural pathways
that my parents did in me.</i></font>

66
00:03:32.795 --> 00:03:34.672
<i><font color="#80FFFF">But I don't wanna live like that anymore.</i></font>

67
00:03:36.841 --> 00:03:39.010
<i><font color="#80FFFF">- I don't wanna live in fear.</i></font>
- [June giggling]

68
00:03:40.511 --> 00:03:42.263
- Oh. fuck.
- [Amy] <i><font color="#80FFFF">I've been holding a lot in.</i></font>

69
00:03:42.263 --> 00:03:44.057
<i><font color="#80FFFF">- but I'm not anymore.</i></font>
- Shit.

70
00:03:44.057 --> 00:03:46.351
[Amy]
<i><font color="#80FFFF">I know it's gonna take a lot of work.</i></font>

71
00:03:46.351 --> 00:03:49.520
<i><font color="#80FFFF">but I really think this is the start
of a new chapter for our family.</i></font>

72
00:03:49.520 --> 00:03:50.647
[Danny] What am I doing?

73
00:03:52.607 --> 00:03:54.692
- I'm really glad we did this.
- Yeah.

74
00:03:56.402 --> 00:03:57.237
Me too.

75
00:04:05.954 --> 00:04:06.996
[vacuum whirring]

76
00:04:06.996 --> 00:04:08.498
[footsteps approaching]

77
00:04:09.874 --> 00:04:10.708
Paul.

78
00:04:11.668 --> 00:04:12.502
Hey.

79
00:04:13.628 --> 00:04:14.462
Yo.

80
00:04:15.880 --> 00:04:18.132
Yo. Paul. I need to talk to you. dude.

81
00:04:18.132 --> 00:04:19.133
Turn that down.

82
00:04:20.468 --> 00:04:21.886
Paul. turn that down.

83
00:04:23.054 --> 00:04:26.015
Paul. turn that shit off. dude.
I almost lit a baby on fire!

84
00:04:26.015 --> 00:04:27.141
[vacuum turns off]

85
00:04:27.725 --> 00:04:29.727
Sounds like you and Isaac are killing it.

86
00:04:30.687 --> 00:04:32.563
Yo. why is this place so clean?

87
00:04:33.815 --> 00:04:36.693
Where you going?
What's with all the new clothes and shit?

88
00:04:37.485 --> 00:04:39.696
Me and Kayla been talking.

89
00:04:39.696 --> 00:04:42.156
If you see something you like.
you go get it.

90
00:04:42.156 --> 00:04:43.074
Right. bro?

91
00:04:44.951 --> 00:04:46.411
She wasn't a bot.

92
00:04:50.790 --> 00:04:52.709
The fuck is happening right now?

93
00:04:52.709 --> 00:04:53.626
Fuck!

94
00:05:02.885 --> 00:05:04.387
Look at this stupid shit.

95
00:05:04.387 --> 00:05:05.596
So happy.

96
00:05:16.024 --> 00:05:17.942
Mom. smile bigger.

97
00:05:17.942 --> 00:05:20.737
Oh. Gosh. she's so strict.

98
00:05:20.737 --> 00:05:23.072
You should've seen her
at the baby cow farm.

99
00:05:23.072 --> 00:05:24.282
[phone buzzes]

100
00:05:25.491 --> 00:05:27.410
