<i><font color=Lime>♪ Sing hallelujah ♪</i></font>

166
00:09:03.459 --> 00:09:09.632
<i><font color=Lime>♪ Christ is risen ♪</i></font>
- [sobbing]

167
00:09:09.632 --> 00:09:14.428
<i><font color=Lime>♪ Oh. what a savior ♪</i></font>

168
00:09:14.428 --> 00:09:19.225
<i><font color=Lime>♪ Isn't he wonderful? ♪</i></font>

169
00:09:19.225 --> 00:09:22.645
<i><font color=Lime>♪ Sing hallelujah ♪</i></font>

170
00:09:22.645 --> 00:09:28.734
<i><font color=Lime>♪ Christ is risen ♪</i></font>

171
00:09:28.734 --> 00:09:33.573
<i><font color=Lime>♪ Bow down before him ♪</i></font>

172
00:09:33.573 --> 00:09:36.033
<i><font color=Lime>♪ For he is Lord of all... ♪</i></font>

173
00:09:36.033 --> 00:09:39.245
[Pastor Kim] Jesus. heavenly God.
please be with my brother.

174
00:09:39.245 --> 00:09:40.955
our new family member.

175
00:09:41.497 --> 00:09:45.084
We ask you to shower him
with your unconditional love.

176
00:09:45.084 --> 00:09:46.252
Thank you.

177
00:09:52.675 --> 00:09:54.051
[Amy] You gotta understand.

178
00:09:54.051 --> 00:09:57.096
George is just very attached
to the Tamago.

179
00:09:57.096 --> 00:09:59.390
- He had it all through his childhood--
- [Jordan] Yeah.

180
00:09:59.390 --> 00:10:01.684
"Tomah-go." "Tomay-go."

181
00:10:03.060 --> 00:10:04.729
Let's talk about your business. Amy.

182
00:10:04.729 --> 00:10:06.480
- Yeah. the business.
- Mm-hm.

183
00:10:06.480 --> 00:10:08.691
You know. it's so crazy.
I read this article

184
00:10:08.691 --> 00:10:11.569
about how millennials
can't afford to have kids.

185
00:10:11.569 --> 00:10:14.989
so they're satisfying
their need to nurture with plants--

186
00:10:14.989 --> 00:10:16.824
Have you ever been to China?

187
00:10:17.742 --> 00:10:18.701
Uh...

188
00:10:19.327 --> 00:10:21.621
Yeah. Once when I was 6.

189
00:10:21.621 --> 00:10:23.039
Only once.

190
00:10:23.539 --> 00:10:24.582
Next time you're there.

191
00:10:24.582 --> 00:10:27.043
you have to check out
the beaches of Sanya.

192
00:10:27.043 --> 00:10:30.338
- Oh. Sanyaaas.
- Yeah!

193
00:10:30.338 --> 00:10:32.590
- Yes.
- [laughing]

194
00:10:32.590 --> 00:10:36.135
See. that's what I'm talking about.
That's how they do business over there.

195
00:10:36.135 --> 00:10:38.512
Spending time together. laughing.

196
00:10:38.512 --> 00:10:41.599
Here in the West.
it's deal points. numbers.

197
00:10:41.599 --> 00:10:42.683
Oh. yeah. yeah.

198
00:10:42.683 --> 00:10:45.353
I definitely prefer
how they do business...

199
00:10:45.853 --> 00:10:47.730
- over there. Yup.
- Mm.

200
00:10:47.730 --> 00:10:49.315
Five-minute reminder.

201
00:10:49.315 --> 00:10:50.816
Pardon me.

202
00:10:50.816 --> 00:10:53.402
I have to go check out some panic rooms.

203
00:10:53.402 --> 00:10:56.697
Smart. I mean.
there's a lot to panic about these days.

204
00:10:56.697 --> 00:10:59.950
Right? Did Naomi show you
that road rage video?

205
00:10:59.950 --> 00:11:01.661
The world's gone completely insane.

206
00:11:01.661 --> 00:11:04.288
She did. It's really terrible.

207
00:11:05.748 --> 00:11:09.460
Why don't you stick around for a while?
We'll continue this when I get back. yeah?

208
00:11:09.460 --> 00:11:11.379
Let me check my schedule first.

209
00:11:11.379 --> 00:11:16.133
You know. Amy. the thing is.
even if the deal looks great on paper.

210
00:11:16.133 --> 00:11:19.720
we still need to
get to know each other as humans.

211
00:11:19.720 --> 00:11:22.306
Make sure we both
feel good about this. right?

212
00:11:23.140 --> 00:11:24.016
Right.

213
00:11:24.517 --> 00:11:25.768
Good.

214
00:11:25.768 --> 00:11:28.270
I'll be back soon. Make yourself at home.

215
00:11:34.777 --> 00:11:35.820
[phone buzzes]

216
00:11:57.842 --> 00:11:59.176
[Veronica] Hey.

217
00:11:59.176 --> 00:12:02.012
- I'm so glad you made it out.
- Good to see you again. Daniel.

218
00:12:02.012 --> 00:12:03.806
Man. you were great up there.

219
00:12:03.806 --> 00:12:06.725
That F sharp you hit was crazy.

220
00:12:06.725 --> 00:12:08.644
- Oh. Thank you.
- [chuckles]

221
00:12:09.812 --> 00:12:12.022
How are you feeling? You doing okay?

222
00:12:12.022 --> 00:12:13.691
Yeah. I think I just...

223
00:12:14.316 --> 00:12:16.485
Think I just needed
a good cry or something.

224
00:12:16.485 --> 00:12:18.821
I'm sorry. I didn't know
what that was about.

225
00:12:18.821 --> 00:12:20.281
You don't have to apologize.

226
00:12:20.281 --> 00:12:23.659
Yeah. I actually break down
all the time up there.

227
00:12:23.659 --> 00:12:24.869
You can let it out.

228
00:12:24.869 --> 00:12:26.495
I appreciate that.

229
00:12:26.495 --> 00:12:28.497
Will we be seeing you regularly?

230
00:12:29.206 --> 00:12:32.543
Um. I live kind of far so--

231
00:12:32.543 --> 00:12:34.962
I think I just needed it this one time.

232
00:12:34.962 --> 00:12:38.591
Well. Edwin always says.
"A church alive is worth the drive."

233
00:12:39.550 --> 00:12:40.551
Right.

